    <item>
      <title>Usage</title>
      <link>https://epvario.github.io/usage/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Sep 2025 11:19:42 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://epvario.github.io/usage/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre-Takeoff:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Press and hold the upper, power button for 3 seconds to turn the device on or off&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Use the side buttons to increase or decrease the volume level&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The Vario will now find your location, the SAT count on the top left will increase &amp;amp; the Flighttimer will show &amp;ldquo;locating&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Once your position is set, the Flighttimer will show &amp;ldquo;&amp;ndash;:&amp;ndash;:&amp;ndash;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;At this stage the vario is in pre-takeoff mode, recoding the past 20 seconds to include your takeoff in the log&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Takeoff:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Firmware</title>
      <link>https://epvario.github.io/firmware/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Sep 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://epvario.github.io/firmware/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;v0.1.3(RC10) &lt;a href=&#34;https://epvario.github.io/firmware/epvario_v0.1.3-RC10_82e895f.uf2&#34;&gt;download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;shutdown screen points to this site&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new: widget altitude gain, which displays difference to 30sec ago&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new: configurable Flight Screen (Default/Numbers)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new configuration elements:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;flight_layout&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;[Default|Numbers]&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;v0.1.3(RC9) &lt;a href=&#34;https://epvario.github.io/firmware/epvario_v0.1.3-RC9_01faa08.uf2&#34;&gt;download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;rebased on master b8361b2&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;improve config deserialization&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;synchronize-igc-record-ticker&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;fix: changed windspeed algorithm (increased prediction by ~40-&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new: optional, configurable shutdown screen to show Owner Details&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new: Temperature based LUT selection to reduce ghosting and washout&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new: configurable vario thresholds (defaults: 0.2m/s und -2.0m/s)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;new configuration elements:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;shutdown_information&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;lt;optional text&amp;gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;climb_threshold&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: 0.2,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;sink_threshold&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: -2.0, &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;v0.1.3(RC7)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Configurator</title>
      <link>https://epvario.github.io/configurator/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Sep 2025 08:00:20 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://epvario.github.io/configurator/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;use with v0.1.3RC10&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Prepare and download your config file and save it to the Vario SD card:&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;style&gt;&#xA;    label, select, input {&#xA;      display: block;&#xA;      margin: 10px 0;&#xA;      width: 100%;&#xA;    }&#xA;    button {&#xA;      margin-top: 20px;&#xA;      padding: 10px;&#xA;    }&#xA;  &lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;label&gt;Pilot Name:&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;text&#34; id=&#34;pilot_name&#34; placeholder=&#34;Your Name, embedded into the IGC File&#34;/&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Glider Type:&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;text&#34; id=&#34;glider_type&#34; placeholder=&#34;Your Wing, embedded into the IGC File&#34;/&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Startup Volume:&#xA;    &lt;select id=&#34;startup_volume&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;Mute&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;Low&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option selected&gt;Medium&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;High&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;Full&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;UTC Time Offset:&#xA;    &lt;select id=&#34;utc_time_offset&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;-0200&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;-0100&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;0000&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;+0100&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option selected&gt;+0200&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Flight Layout:&#xA;    &lt;select id=&#34;flight_layout&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option selected&gt;Default&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;      &lt;option&gt;Numbers&lt;/option&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/select&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Display Version (1 to 3):&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;display_version&#34; min=&#34;1&#34; max=&#34;3&#34; value=&#34;1&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Climb Threshold:&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;climb_threshold&#34; min=&#34;0&#34; max=&#34;10&#34; value=&#34;0.2&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Sink Threshold:&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;number&#34; id=&#34;sink_threshold&#34; min=&#34;-10&#34; max=&#34;0&#34; value=&#34;-2.0&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;Shutdown Information:&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;text&#34; id=&#34;shutdown_information&#34; placeholder=&#34;will remain visible after shut down&#34;/&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;button onclick=&#34;generateConfig()&#34;&gt;Download Config&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;script&gt;&#xA;    function generateConfig() {&#xA;      const config = {&#xA;        pilot_name: document.getElementById(&#39;pilot_name&#39;).value,&#xA;        glider_type: document.getElementById(&#39;glider_type&#39;).value,&#xA;        startup_volume: document.getElementById(&#39;startup_volume&#39;).value,&#xA;        utc_time_offset: document.getElementById(&#39;utc_time_offset&#39;).value,&#xA;        flight_layout: document.getElementById(&#39;flight_layout&#39;).value,&#xA;&#xA;        climb_threshold: Number (parseFloat( document.getElementById(&#39;climb_threshold&#39;).value).toFixed(1)) ,&#xA;        sink_threshold: Number (parseFloat( document.getElementById(&#39;sink_threshold&#39;).value).toFixed(1)) ,&#xA;        shutdown_information: document.getElementById(&#39;shutdown_information&#39;).value,&#xA;      };&#xA;&#xA;      const displayVersion = document.getElementById(&#39;display_version&#39;).value;&#xA;      if (displayVersion &amp;&amp; parseInt(displayVersion) &gt;= 1 &amp;&amp; parseInt(displayVersion) &lt;= 3) {&#xA;        config.display_version = parseInt(displayVersion);&#xA;      }&#xA;&#xA;      const jsonString = JSON.stringify(config, null, 2);&#xA;      const blob = new Blob([jsonString], { type: &#39;text/plain&#39; });&#xA;      const link = document.createElement(&#39;a&#39;);&#xA;      link.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);&#xA;      link.download = &#39;config.txt&#39;;&#xA;      link.click();&#xA;    }&#xA;  &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Elevation</title>
      <link>https://epvario.github.io/elevation/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Sep 2025 08:00:29 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://epvario.github.io/elevation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Your EPVario can utilize NASAs SRTM Terrain Data and calculate your approximate altitude above ground above a 90x90m grid on your location.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You need to download and extract the tiles of your flying region to your SD card.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://epvario.github.io/agl.html&#34;&gt;click here to open our map&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Code</title>
      <link>https://epvario.github.io/software/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://epvario.github.io/software/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;developer-quickstart&#34;&gt;Developer quickstart:&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install the Rust toolchain using &lt;strong&gt;rustup&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a href=&#34;https://rustup.rs/&#34;&gt;https://rustup.rs/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install the nightly toolchain and add the target to build for the RP2040:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustup toolchain install nightly&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustup target add thumbv6m-none-eabi&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;To build the firmware to flash it via the BOOTSEL mode, you need &lt;a href=&#34;https://crates.io/crates/elf2uf2-rs&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;elf2uf2-rs&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cargo install elf2uf2-rs&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;To build the firmware to flash it with the BOOTSEL mode, from the &lt;code&gt;firmware&lt;/code&gt; folder run:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cargo build --release&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;elf2uf2-rs ./target/thumbv6m-none-eabi/release/ep-vario-firmware ep-vario-firmware.uf2 &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;With the EPVario turned off, connect it to your computer using a USB-C cable. Hold the Up button and press and hold the power button for 2 seconds. A mass storage device should show up on your computer. Drag and drop the &lt;code&gt;ep-vario-firmware.uf2&lt;/code&gt; file that was just created to the device. It will automatically dismount the device and install the firmware.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Hardware</title>
      <link>https://epvario.github.io/hardware/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Sep 2025 07:35:25 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://epvario.github.io/hardware/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features:&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RP2040&lt;/strong&gt;, dual-core Arm Cortex-M0+ processor&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;power saving Epaper, WeAct Studio &lt;strong&gt;2.9 Inch Epaper&lt;/strong&gt; Module&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;3.3V architecture using TPS6303 voltage regulator&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L5M6DS3&lt;/strong&gt; IMU for accelerometer and gyro data fusion&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BMP280&lt;/strong&gt; pressure sensor&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;M10UBX&lt;/strong&gt; GPS module (supporting GLONASS, BDSB, GALILEO, SBAS, QZSS)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;QMC5883 compass&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MicroSD&lt;/strong&gt; cardslot for flight path logging&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1W speaker&lt;/strong&gt; for excellent acustic (30x20cm)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;USB-C&lt;/strong&gt; connector&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;MAX90357AEWL+T speaker amplifier&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;integrated &lt;strong&gt;1100mAh Lipo&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;USB-C lipo charger (MCP73871)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;user interface with 3 buttons&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;compact size and low weight (80-85g)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;over 15h runtime&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;required-components&#34;&gt;Required components:&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;epVario PCB&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;WeAct Studio 2.9&amp;quot; EPaper Module&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Walksnail WS-M181 GPS + compass&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;EEMB LP603449 1100mAh lipo battery (51x35x6.3mm)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Adafruit 4227 1W 8 Ohm Speaker or similiar (30x20mm)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;microSD card, not larger than 32GB (preferably SanDisk)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;3D printed case&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
